<form action="/auth/index.html/u" id="regform" method="post" title="Form used by registered users to login">
<input type="text" name="user" id="user" size="25" class="text" accesskey="u" />
<input id="password" name="password" type="password" size="25" class="text" accesskey="p" />
<input type="submit" name="Login" value="Log In" class="button" id='submitbutton' />
To login, follow the instructions in the panel on left.
Once authenticated you will be given limited Internet access for the
duration of your session. You should be able to browse the web, access
email, make SSH connections, run VPN and print. For more details see
The following IPv4 protocols are allowed, outbound: HTTP, HTTPS,
SSL, IMAPS, SSL-SMTP, IPSEC VPN. Incoming connections are not
Please note that there is a 10 minute inactivity
timeout on your authenticated session, so you may be called upon to
re-authenticate if this period is exceeded.
University of Manchester staff and students may launch the local VPN
client for full Internet access without having to complete this
Visitors may similarly launch their IPSEC VPN client as normal to
receive the level of access determined by the home institution. No
